banks_kt_tunstall-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/azealia_banks_kt_tunstall-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/azealia_banks_kt_tunstall-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/azealia_banks_kt_tunstall-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>在<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/azealia-banks">Azealia Banks</a>对<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/beyonce">Beyoncé</a>的新专辑《Cowboy Carter》发表评论后，Azealia Banks 和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kt-tunstall">KT Tunstall</a>建立了一种意想不到的友谊。</p><p>班克斯公开批评贝伊女王受乡村音乐影响的新音乐方向，将其描述为<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/azealia-banks-slams-beyonces-cowboy-carter-as-white-women-cosplay-3607552">“白人女性角色扮演”</a> ，并表示<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/azealia-banks-tells-beyonce-youre-setting-yourself-up-to-be-ridiculed-again-over-new-country-album-3586845">她觉得这位歌手“让自己受到嘲笑”。</a></p><p>在听到这张专辑后，班克斯最近一次爆发，​​抱怨<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/taylor-swift">泰勒·斯威夫特</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kacey-musgraves">凯西·马斯格雷夫斯</a>缺席，然后声称<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/azealia-banks-personally-would-have-jumped-out-of-seat-for-a-kt-tunstall-appearance-on-beyonces-cowboy-carter-3610940">她“个人会从我的座位上跳起来参加 KT Tunstall 的演出”</a> 。</p><p> Tunstall 通过分享<i>NME</i>的文章来回应这一评论，随后在社交媒体上回复，开玩笑地写道：“公平地说，我会 100% 从沙发上站起来。”</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">公平地说，我会 100% 离开沙发<a href="https://t.co/RtqSkiJVxX">https://t.co/RtqSkiJVxX</a></p><p> - KT Tunstall (@KTTunstall) <a href="https://twitter.com/KTTunstall/status/1773775472297422969?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2024 年 3 月 29 日</a></p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p>双方的争论仍在继续，班克斯引用了 Tunstall 的回应，并在 Instagram 上回复道：“《突然我看见》是我最喜欢的歌曲之一@kttunstall！我还在敲那个下巴！！” </p><blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink